# Module: `packages/math`

- Pure functions only — no side effects, no external imports outside this package
- Always use `GlobalPoint` or `LocalPoint` from `types.ts` — never plain `{ x, y }` objects
  - `GlobalPoint` — coordinates in the scene/world space
  - `LocalPoint` — coordinates local to an element
  - The legacy `Point` type alias does not exist; use the specific typed variants
- Functions must be unit-tested

## How to verify

```bash
# No external imports (outside packages/math itself):
grep -rn "^import" packages/math/src/ \
  | grep -v "from \"@excalidraw/math\|from \"\./\|from \"\.\./"

# No plain { x, y } object literals used as point types (excludes tests and pointFrom converters):
grep -rn "{ x:" packages/math/src/ \
  | grep -v "\.test\.\|pointFrom\|__mocks__"

# Ensure no usage of the removed legacy Point type (GlobalPoint/LocalPoint should be used):
grep -rn "\bPoint\b" packages/math/src/ \
  | grep -v "GlobalPoint\|LocalPoint\|\.test\.\|Polygon<Point\|Curve<Point\|Ellipse<Point"

# Run math unit tests:
yarn test:app packages/math
```
